0%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theparisreview.org%2Fblog%2F2015%2F07%2F23%2Fthe-library-of-babel-as-seen-from-within%2F%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3ESeen%20from%20Within%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Felectricliterature.com%2Fputting-borges-infinite-library-on-the-internet-1e26c286c5a%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3ETower%20of%20Babel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Funinventional.html%22%3EUninventional%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22sidebar%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Flibraryofbabel.info%22%3EBack%20to%20Portal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22left%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A110px%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EMy%20thinking%20about%20this%20story%20has%20developed%2C%20and%20my%20research%20has%20continued%2C%20since%20I%20wrote%20these%20pages.%20I%20have%20corrected%20and%20expanded%20upon%20them%20in%20%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fpunctumbooks.com%2Ftitles%2Ftar-for-mortar%2F%22%20class%3D%22intext%22%3ETar%20for%20Mortar%3A%20%22The%20Library%20of%20Babel%22%20and%20the%20Dream%20of%20Totality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20available%20open%20access%20from%20punctum%20books.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20paragraph%20of%20Borges%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fmaskofreason.files.wordpress.com%2F2011%2F02%2Fthe-library-of-babel-by-jorge-luis-borges.pdf%22%3EThe%20Library%20of%20Babel%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20offers%20a%20minute%20description%20of%20the%20universe%20he%20has%20doomed%20his%20librarians%20to%20inhabit.%20Which%20is%20why%20I%20was%20shocked%20to%20reread%20the%20story%20recently%20and%20discover%20my%20mental%20image%20was%20completely%20wrong.%20He%20describes%20a%20vast%20architecture%20of%20interconnecting%20hexagons%20each%20with%20four%20walls%20of%20bookshelves%20and%20passageways%20leading%20to%20other%20identical%20hexagons.%20I%20had%20made%20the%20assumption%20that%20six%20walls%20minus%20four%20walls%20of%20book%20shelves%20equals%20two%20such%20passageways.%20I%20read%20to%20my%20astonishment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20arrangement%20of%20the%20galleries%20is%20always%20the%20same%3A%20Twenty%20bookshelves%2C%20five%20to%20each%20side%2C%20line%20four%20of%20the%20hexagon's%20six%20sides%3B%20the%20height%20of%20the%20bookshelves%2C%20floor%20to%20ceiling%2C%20is%20hardly%20greater%20than%20the%20height%20of%20a%20normal%20librarian.%20One%20of%20the%20hexagon's%20free%20sides%20opens%20onto%20a%20narrow%20sort%20of%20vestibule%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20opens%20onto%20another%20gallery%2C%20identical%20to%20the%20first-identical%20in%20fact%20to%20all.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOne%3C%2Fi%3E%20of%20the%20hexagon%E2%80%99s%20free%20sides%20opens%20onto%20a%20vestibule%20-%20how%20could%20this%20be%3F%20So%20much%20of%20the%20story%20told%20by%20our%20narrator%20conjures%20endless%2C%20desolate%20expanses%20of%20hexagons%2C%20repeating%20infinitely%20and%20inspiring%20both%20the%20reverence%20of%20the%20God%20who%20created%20them%20and%20despair%20at%20a%20life%20trapped%20inside%20them.%20But%20this%20would%20only%20be%20possible%20if%20the%20hexagons%20had%20two%20openings%20each%20-%20otherwise%20the%20structure%20would%20terminate%20at%20its%20first%20junction.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22right2%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A375px%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%20class%3D%22theory%22%20title%3D%22Illustration%20by%20Cristina%20Grau%22%20alt%3D%22Four%20hexagons%20each%20with%20a%20single%20opening%20terminate%20in%20a%20central%20chamber%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A225px%3B%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22left%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A340px%22%3E%0A%3Cp%3EI%20found%20an%20answer%20in%20Antonio%20Toca%20Fernandez%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.uam.mx%2Fdifusion%2Fcasadeltiempo%2F24_iv_oct_2009%2Fcasa_del_tiempo_eIV_num24_77_80.pdf%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3E%E2%80%9CLa%20Biblioteca%20de%20Babel%3A%20Una%20Modesta%20Propuesta%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20which%20I%20am%20greatly%20indebted.%20The%20first%20version%20of%20Borges%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9CLa%20Biblioteca%20de%20Babel%E2%80%9D%2C%20published%20in%201941%2C%20contained%20the%20same%20description%2C%20excepting%20two%20words%3A%20each%20hexagon%20contained%2025%20bookshelves%2C%20five%20each%20covering%20five%20walls.%20In%201956%20Borges%20changed%20the%20text%2C%20presumably%20because%20he%20had%20recognized%20his%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20trickiest%20part%3A%20he%20changed%20twenty-five%20to%20twenty%2C%20changed%20%E2%80%9Ceach%20of%20the%20walls%20less%20one%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Ceach%20of%20the%20walls%20less%20two%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20left%20only%20a%20single%20opening%20to%20an%20adjacent%20hexagon.%20Such%20an%20edit%20is%20incomprehensible%20unless%20Borges%20intended%20to%20open%20the%20fifth%20wall%20as%20another%20passage%20allowing%20for%20the%20interminable%20continuity%20of%20his%20labyrinth.%20It's%20almost%20as%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20the%20author%20recognizing%20two%20of%20his%20errors%20in%20this%20short%20phrase%20while%20creating%20a%20third.%20That%20must%20be%20the%20case%2C%20unless%20he%20had%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20labyrinth%20in%20which%20only%20his%20most%20careful%20readers%20would%20become%20lost%2C%20consisting%20of%20an%20impossible%20yoking%20of%20inconsistent%20architectures%20and%20irreconcilable%20texts.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20accept%20the%20reading%20that%20each%20hexagon%20has%20two%20connections%20to%20adjacent%20chambers%2C%20this%20still%20leaves%20a%20great%20diversity%20of%20possible%20organizations.%20The%20easiest%20assumption%20to%20make%20is%20that%20each%20hexagon%20has%20its%20passages%20on%20two%20opposing%20walls%2C%20creating%20a%20continuous%20pathway.%20This%20structure%20presents%20a%20problem%2C%20however%20(see%20adjacent).%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22right2%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A495px%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%3E%3Cimg%20class%3D%22theory%22%20title%3D%22Illustration%20by%20Sarah%20Basile%22%20alt%3D%22A%20grid%20of%20hexagons%20each%20with%20two%20openings.%20A%20series%20of%20parallel%20paths%20passes%20through%20them%20diagonally.%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A460px%3B%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22left%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A630px%22%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThese%20paths%20would%20persist%20as%20such%20to%20infinity%2C%20without%20the%20librarians%20of%20one%20corridor%20ever%20being%20able%20to%20cross%20the%20minuscule%20distance%20separating%20them%20from%20the%20adjacent%20throughways.%20They%20might%20be%20separated%20by%20no%20more%20than%20a%20bookshelf%20throughout%20their%20lifetime%20from%20others%20they%20could%20never%20reach.%20Borges%20does%20say%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20hexagons%20are%20tiered%2C%20with%20each%20level%20connected%20by%20vertiginous%20spiral%20staircases.%20If%20the%20passages%20above%20or%20below%20had%20a%20slightly%20transposed%20arrangement%20(see%20adjacent)%2C%20then%20the%20parallel%20corridors%20could%20be%20accessed%20by%20going%20up%20one%20flight%20of%20stairs%2C%20passing%20to%20an%20adjacent%20hexagon%2C%20and%20descending%20again.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22right3%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A%20565px%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%20class%3D%22theory%22%20title%3D%22Illustration%20by%20Sarah%20Basile%22%20alt%3D%22a%20grid%20of%20hexagons.%20A%20series%20of%20parallel%20paths%20passes%20through%20them%20vertically.%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A683px%3B%20%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22left%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A785px%22%3E%0A%3Cp%3EWould%20it%20be%20possible%20for%20all%20the%20hexagons%20on%20a%20single%20floor%20to%20be%20connected%3F%20This%20would%20require%20a%20more%20complex%20design.%20Imagine%20a%20path%20radiating%20from%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccentral%E2%80%9D%20chamber%20(in%20the%20library%2C%20as%20in%20the%20infinite%20sphere%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexact%20center%20is%20any%20hexagon%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccircumference%20is%20unattainable%E2%80%9D).%20Such%20a%20path%20quickly%20encounters%20a%20problem%20(see%20adjacent).%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20path%20must%20either%20return%20on%20itself%2C%20creating%20a%20closed%20circuit%20inaccessible%20to%20the%20outside%20(there%20is%20one%20somewhat%20cryptic%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20hexagon%20in%20circuit%2015-94%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20story%20-%20the%20circuits%20that%20the%20librarians%20have%20numbered%20may%20be%20just%20such%20self-contained%20patterns)%2C%20or%20radiate%20outwards%2C%20leaving%20the%20central%20hexagon%20with%20only%20one%20opening.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22right3%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A825px%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cimg%20class%3D%22theory%22%20title%3D%22Illustration%20by%20Sarah%20Basile%22%20alt%3D%22A%20single%20path%20emerges%20from%20a%20central%20hexagon%2C%20circles%20once%2C%20and%20terminates%20by%20reconnecting%20to%20the%20first%20hexagon.%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A885px%3B%20%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22left%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A965px%22%3E%0A%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20believe%2C%20as%20does%20our%20narrator-librarian%2C%20in%20the%20infinity%20of%20the%20library%2C%20there%20must%20be%20at%20all%20times%20two%20open%20paths%2C%20two%20%E2%80%9Cliberties%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20Go%20players%20would%20call%20them%20(see%20adjacent).%20Two%20paths%20emerge%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccentral%E2%80%9D%20chamber%20(there%20are%20only%20ever%20relative%20centers%20in%20such%20a%20structure)%2C%20and%20reunite%20at%20infinity%2C%20which%20is%20another%20way%20of%20saying%20they%20never%20meet.%20If%20one%20of%20these%20paths%20simply%20came%20to%20an%20end%2C%20reaching%20a%20hexagon%20with%20no%20hexagons%20beyond%20it%2C%20that%20hexagon%20would%20have%20only%20one%20entrance%2C%20breaking%20the%20symmetry%20established%20by%20Borges.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EA%20strange%20realization%20lurks%20in%20this%20design%3A%20if%20we%20extend%20its%20spiral%20by%20a%20few%20more%20involutions%2C%20it%20would%20become%2C%20within%20the%20limits%20of%20our%20frame%20of%20reference%2C%20indistinguishable%20from%20the%20design%20with%20which%20we%20started.%20Those%20paths%20which%20seemed%20to%20stretch%20out%20to%20infinity%2C%20lonely%20and%20isolated%2C%20could%20actually%20have%20been%20switchbacks%2C%20connected%20at%20great%20distances.%20This%20structure%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20Richard%20Feynman%E2%80%99s%20metaphoric%20description%20of%20antimatter%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20as%20though%20a%20bombardier%20flying%20low%20over%20a%20road%20suddenly%20sees%20three%20roads%20and%20it%20is%20only%20when%20two%20of%20them%20come%20together%20and%20disappear%20again%20that%20he%20realizes%20that%20he%20has%20simply%20passed%20over%20a%20long%20switchback%20in%20a%20single%20road.%E2%80%9D%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20difference%2C%20at%20the%20extreme%20reaches%20of%20an%20infinite%20structure%20like%20the%20one%20we%20are%20imagining%2C%20between%20the%20seemingly%20fragmented%20structure%20with%20which%20we%20began%20and%20the%20seemingly%20unified%20one%20we%20have%20reached.%20A%20finite%20creature%20could%20at%20most%20only%20believe%20that%20the%20interminable%20corridors%20met%20at%20infinity%2C%20without%20ever%20reaching%20that%20point.%20%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22right2%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A1090px%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%20class%3D%22theory%22%20title%3D%22Illustration%20by%20Sarah%20Basile%22%20alt%3D%22Two%20paths%20emerge%20from%20either%20side%20of%20a%20central%20hexagon%20and%20radiate%20outwards%20in%20a%20spiral%20design.%20This%20design%20could%20continue%20as%20such%20infinitely.%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A1055px%3B%20%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22leftlast%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20invokes%20one%20of%20Borges%E2%80%99%20favorite%20themes%2C%20the%20line%20and%20the%20circle%20as%20they%20relate%20to%20the%20infinity%20or%20finitude%20of%20existence.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20Borges%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Death%20and%20the%20Compass%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9CLa%20Muerte%20y%20La%20Br%C3%BAjula%E2%80%9D)%2C%20the%20trapped%20protagonist%20longs%20only%20for%20a%20simpler%20labyrinth%3A%20%22There%20are%20three%20lines%20too%20many%20in%20your%20labyrinth%E2%80%A6I%20know%20of%20a%20Greek%20labyrinth%20that%20is%20but%20one%20straight%20line.%E2%80%9D%20And%20his%20captor%20replies%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20next%20time%20I%20kill%20you%E2%80%A6I%20promise%20you%20the%20labyrinth%20that%20consists%20of%20a%20single%20straight%20line%20that%20is%20indivisible%20and%20endless.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3EWe%20too%20could%20imagine%20a%20simpler%20labyrinth%2C%20a%20single%20string%20of%20hexagons%20too%20long%20for%20any%20mortal%20to%20traverse%2C%20without%20the%20capacious%20pits%20that%20grant%20a%20view%20on%20infinity%20and%20the%20knowledge%20of%20other%20paths.%20Anyone%20with%20the%20misfortune%20to%20find%20themselves%20inside%20such%20a%20space%20would%20never%20know%20if%20she%20walked%20an%20infinite%20line%20or%20a%20circle%2C%20if%20the%20ends%20of%20her%20path%20met%20or%20not.%20An%20infinite%20circle%2C%20Borges%20points%20out%20in%20another%20tale%20(%E2%80%9CIbn-Hakam%20al%20Bokhari%2C%20Murdered%20in%20His%20Labyrinth%E2%80%9D)%2C%20would%20be%2C%20for%20finite%20eyes%2C%20indistinguishable%20from%20a%20line%20(were%20its%20circumference%20visible%20at%20all).%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6They%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20labyrinth.%20Seen%20at%20close%20range%2C%20it%20looked%20like%20a%20straight%2C%20virtually%20interminable%20wall%E2%80%A6Dunraven%20said%20it%20made%20a%20circle%3B%20but%20one%20so%20broad%20its%20curvature%20was%20imperceptible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3EThese%20lines%20immediately%20follow%20the%20complaint%20of%20his%20companion%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%98Mysteries%20ought%20to%20be%20simple.%20Remember%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20Purloined%20letter%2C%20remember%20Zangwill%E2%80%99s%20locked%20room.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%98Or%20complex%2C%E2%80%99%20replied%20Dunraven.%20%E2%80%98Remember%20the%20universe.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Chr%20class%3D%22theory%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A1165px%3B%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22theorybottom2%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A1165px%3B%20left%3A%2050px%3B%20width%3A%20700px%3B%20height%3A55px%3B%20text-align%3A%20center%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cp%3E%26nbsp%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22theorybottom%22%20style%3D%22position%3A%20relative%3B%20top%3A1165px%3B%20left%3A%2050px%3B%20width%3A%20700px%3B%20height%3A55px%3B%20text-align%3A%20center%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cb%3EWhy%20Hexagons%20Pt.%201%3C%2Fb%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22%2Ftheory2.html%22%3EWhy%20Hexagons%20pt.%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22%2Ftheory3.html%22%3EAlphabets%20%20%26amp%3B%20Irony%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22%2Ftheory4.html%22%3EGrains%20of%20Sand%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Flibraryofbabel.info%22%3EBack%20to%20Portal%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Flibrary.oapen.org%2Fviewer%2Fweb%2Fviewer.html%3Ffile%3D%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F20.500.12657%2F25433%2F1004662.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26amp%3BisAllowed%3Dy%22%3ETar%20for%20Mortar%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fpunctumbooks.com%2Ftitles%2Fmassa-por-argamassa-a-biblioteca-de-babel-e-o-sonho-de-totalidade%2F%22%3EMassa%20por%20Argamassa%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theparisreview.org%2Fblog%2F2015%2F07%2F23%2Fthe-library-of-babel-as-seen-from-within%2F%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3ESeen%20from%20Within%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Felectricliterature.com%2Fputting-borges-infinite-library-on-the-internet-1e26c286c5a%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3ETower%20of%20Babel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20class%3D%22intext%2